# Changelog on every commit + push

Whenever you create a git commit that will be pushed, you MUST record the
change in `CHANGELOG.md` at the repo root, in the SAME commit.

- Add a new entry at the TOP of the file (newest first).
- Each entry starts with a date-time heading in IST:
  `## YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM IST — <short title>`
- Under it, list concise bullets describing what changed and why.
- Stage `CHANGELOG.md` together with the code so they land in one commit.

Example:

```markdown
## 2026-06-20 22:26 IST — Email validation on signup
- Reject disposable/undeliverable emails before account creation.
- Add /auth/confirm route to complete the email verification link.
```
